Where available, the Services may provide you with links to third-party processors to process transactions such as fiat purchases of Digital Tokens, sale of Digital Tokens, exchange of Digital Tokens, and other functionalities which may be available in the future. You can see what third-party services are available within World App. When you perform these transactions, you are making transactions with third parties and not us. You must follow the relevant instructions provided by the third-party provider and accept their terms of service. We do not take control of or transmit your funds or Digital Tokens at any time while providing our Services, or when you access third-party services.
2.6 Peer-to-Peer Transactions.
The Services provide a communications platform through which you may send to, or request, receive, and store supported Digital Tokens from, other blockchain wallets, whether controlled by you or third parties. Your transfer of supported Digital Tokens between your other blockchain wallets and to and from third parties is a transfer. The party initiating the transfer is solely responsible for executing the transaction properly, which may include, among other things, payment of sufficient network or miner’s fees in order for the transaction to be successful. Insufficient network fees may cause a transfer to remain in a pending state and may result in delays or loss incurred as a result of an error in the initiation of the transaction. We have no obligation to assist in the remediation of such transactions. When you send any Digital Token from your wallet to another blockchain wallet, such transfers are executed on chain by you and not under our control. You should verify all transaction information prior to submitting them. We bear no liability or responsibility in the event you enter an incorrect blockchain destination address. Digital Token transfers cannot be reversed once they have been broadcast to the relevant blockchain network, although they may be in a pending state, and designated accordingly, while the transaction is processed by network operators. We do not control the network and make no guarantees that a transfer will be confirmed by the network.
2.7 Vault
2.7.1 General information.
World App provides the user interface to a decentralized “vault” for your Digital Tokens (“Vault”). Your use of the Vault constitutes your acknowledgment and acceptance of the terms governing the Vault, as well as any additional terms provided by third parties that have developed or provide features relating to or arising out of your use of the Vault.
Vault only supports certain Digital Tokens. These Digital Tokens do not qualify as Asset Referenced Tokens or E-Money Tokens, in the terms set by Regulation (EU) 2023/1114 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 31 May 2023 on markets in crypto-assets. The supported Digital Tokens will be displayed in World App when accessing your Vault. The Digital Tokens supported by the Vault may change from time to time, and there is no guarantee that supported Digital Tokens will remain available for use in the Vault.
Vault is provided in connection with third-party smart contracts. No other person or entity, besides you, has the ability to interact with your Vault or the Digital Tokens inside your Vault. Neither TFH nor any third-party has administrative keys or access (privileged or otherwise) to your Vault or the associated smart contracts. A deposit into, or withdrawal from, the Vault of any Digital Tokens for your account can only occur if such a transaction is signed with your corresponding private key(s) described in Section 2.1 of these Terms. This means that if you lose access to or control of your private key(s), you will not be able to make any deposits or withdrawals of Digital Tokens from the Vault and no other party will be able to assist you or do so on your behalf. Accordingly, use of the Vault does not, and cannot, provide to you any custody, bailment, or transfer services by TFH or any other third party with respect to any Digital Tokens you may lock up using the Vault on your account.
The smart contract governing the Vault functions for WLD tokens can be viewed using the blockchain here. For clarity, use of these and any other related Vault functions are subject to the same Disclaimer of Warranties contained in Section 12 of these Terms.
2.7.2 Vault Functions
. Vault currently offers the following features, which may be altered, removed, or added to by TFH or third parties: Locking, Yield, Withdrawal and Security Period, Grants to Vault.
2.7.3 Locking
. By using Vault, you agree to lock your Digital Tokens for a set period of time. Locking Digital Tokens using your Vault will transfer those Digital Tokens from your non-custodial wallet to a decentralized smart contract. Upon transfer, these Digital Tokens will become “locked” in the vault, which includes the period during which they remain deposited in the Vault as well as a pre-determined duration called a “Security Period,” which is described in more detail below. While your Digital Tokens are locked, you will not be able to access, transfer, or perform any other transaction using them until you have requested to withdraw them and allowed the applicable Security Period to elapse. No one, including TFH or the third party Provider, has the ability to unlock, custody, control, withdraw or transfer your locked Digital Tokens. Placing your Digital Tokens into the Vault and subjecting them to the locking and withdrawal restrictions does not constitute a sale, loan, or transfer of any rights, title, or interest in the Digital Tokens to TFH or any other third party.
Locking your Digital Tokens in Vault does not guarantee the safekeeping or custody of your Digital Tokens. No deposit insurance scheme, or any similar safeguard, applies to your Digital Tokens, and the value and/or utility of any Digital Tokens you have locked up may increase or decrease throughout the duration of the Security Period. This means the value or utility of any Digital Tokens you lock up in your Vault may decrease, or go to zero during the Security Period. You acknowledge and agree that any withdrawal of Digital Tokens on your account after the applicable Security Period may result in the return of Digital Tokens that have a lower value, or no value, than they had at the time you locked them in your Vault, and that TFH nor any third party bears the risk or responsibility of any diminution in value that may occur.
2.7.4 Yield.
You may also be eligible to generate what, for purposes of this product, is referred to as “yield” on certain Digital Tokens in your Vault. This yield, which may take the form of additional Digital Tokens, is provided by a third party via a separate series of smart contract operations that you may access using the interface provided within World App. Neither TFH nor any third party uses, assumes control of, receives any credit for, or otherwise disposes of your Digital Tokens. As such, yield is not interest that is tied to or generated by anything other than the locking up of your Digital Tokens according to the terms and specifications provided. Any yield you may receive is provided to you as a grant by the third party based on your decisions to store Digital Tokens using the Vault. The specifications determining the generation of yield, including the amount generated or the time over which it may accrue, may be changed or canceled at any time, at the discretion of the third party Provider.
There may be a maximum amount of yield you can earn. These details will be displayed alongside your Vault and via any additional terms provided by the third party (identified as the “Provider” within the World App) providing the yield. These additional terms are also incorporated into these Terms. Yield is not provided or serviced by TFH.
Any yield that accrues will only be distributed to you upon the completion of withdrawal for any yield-generating Digital Tokens from the Vault, which occurs only after any applicable Security Period expires. This withdrawal is the final condition of any yield grant, meaning you have no right, title, or interest in any yield that has generated or will be generated unless and until such time as the yield has been received in your non-custodial wallet. This also means that if you lose access to or control of your private key(s), you will not be able to make any withdrawals that will entitle you to receive yield.
2.7.5 Withdrawal and Security Period.
You may initiate a withdrawal of your Digital Tokens from your Vault at any time. The Digital Tokens you have requested to withdraw from your Vault will be returned to you after a pre-set duration of time called the “Security Period” has elapsed. Each time you initiate a withdrawal of Digital Tokens from the Vault, a new Security Period will start and count down the time until those Digital Tokens will be returned to you. During this time, the Digital Tokens you have selected to withdraw will remain locked, and you may also cancel your withdrawal. Once the Security Period has elapsed, your withdrawal will be complete and the Digital Tokens, along with any generated yield that may have accrued, will be sent to your wallet. The duration of the Security Period will be stated within World App when you access your Vault.
2.7.6 Grants to Vault.
This feature, once selected, allows you to automatically send WLD Grants directly to the Vault on your account instead of to your wallet. You can change this setting at any time.
2.7.7 TFH and Vault.
The access to this feature is made via World App. However, TFH will only be able to read related data and display it to you. TFH cannot transfer, withdraw or deposit any of your Digital Tokens and does not have any access to your Vault.
