2.10 World ID interface.
The World Foundation, and not TFH, stewards the World ID Protocol and controls the Orb related data processing to verify a World ID. We may make your World ID available to you (as an interface) through the Service. The World ID Protocol allows you to prove you are a real and unique human being while protecting your privacy.
2.11 Invite Program.
Where available, we may make the ‘Invite’ feature available to you. Using Invite, you can invite friends and family to download World App and get verified for World ID. If you are using Invite you agree to the following terms and conditions:
Rewards for participating in Invite are provided by World Assets Limited. World Assets Limited may, in its sole discretion, offer you a reward for inviting users that successfully verify their World ID. In order to receive the reward, you must meet certain conditions, which will be explained to you in World App. You have a maximum limit of how many users you can refer to World App. This limit is displayed in World App.
No purchase is necessary to participate in the Invite feature. Invite is only available for personal, non-commercial use. You may only use the Invite feature in good faith for lawful purposes. You may not: (a) use Invite or the Services in a deceptive, fraudulent or unlawful manner; (b) do anything to damage our brand, goodwill or reputation; (c) transmit unsolicited or unauthorized advertising or promotional material; (d) make false or misleading claims; (e) use paid search, paid media or other similar activity to solicit users via Invite; and (f) use Invite to try to obtain personal information from other users.
Invite is not available in all countries or locations and is not available to all users. Participation in Invite is not available in any jurisdiction where all or any portion of this feature may violate (or cause us to violate) any legal requirements. You agree not to use Invite if the Invite feature is not in accordance with applicable law in your location.
Invite is made available at our sole discretion. We may change, modify, suspend and cancel the feature at any time. World Assets Limited may refuse to offer you a reward for inviting users to verify their World ID where it determines, in its sole discretion, that you have violated these Terms.
2.12 WLD Grants & Reservations.
One of the Third Party services is claiming a small amount of WLD at different intervals (“WLD Grants”). WLD Grants are provided by World Assets Limited, a subsidiary of the Worldcoin Foundation. Exact amounts, intervals, and timings of both WLD Grants will be specified in World App, but are determined solely by World Assets Limited. Consistent with prior versions of these terms, the previously available WLD Reservations do not guarantee that you will receive any amount of WLD Grants. Exact amounts, intervals, and timings of WLD Reservations will be specified in World App, but are determined solely by World Assets Limited. WLD Reservations may expire, with or without prior notice in World App, regardless of whether you have already made a WLD Reservation or received the associated WLD Grant. They are revocable at the sole discretion of World Assets Limited.
2.13 Operator App.
For Orb Operators and other partners, we make available an Operator App that allows you to monitor certain activity and statistics relevant to you and your business as Orb Operators. We may also make certain features available to help you conduct your business as Orb Operators.
2.14 Miniapps
. “Miniapps” is a feature of World App that allows you to access a platform of mini applications that can be accessed within World App. We have sole discretion of determining how Miniapps are displayed within World App. You must have a World App wallet address to access Miniapps.
You acknowledge that in displaying Miniapps, TFH is providing a technology platform only connecting users. At no time does TFH transmit, store, take possession of, custody, or otherwise engage with any traditional or digital currency. TFH does not process transactions, act as a payment processor, or otherwise become involved in processing transactions. TFH is not a party to the transactions and has no liability in regards to these transactions. TFH is unable to provide support in regards to transaction problems.
2.14.1 Transactions and Payments related to Miniapps.
Miniapps are displayed within World App and may offer goods or services World App users may buy using Digital Tokens in their World App wallets. These transactions occur between you and the miniapp. TFH is not party to any such transaction.
With respect to any such transactions, you acknowledge that World App wallet is a non-custodial service, that TFH does not store or custody your Digital Tokens and does not transact, transmit, take possession of, or otherwise have any involvement with making any transactions. Digital Tokens are always stored and transmitted on their respective blockchain networks. There are no guarantees the transactions will process correctly.
TFH only connects you to a third-party in the Miniapps platform and is not a party to any transactions. TFH has no role in processing payments and governing refund or cancellation charges.
Once you decide to engage in a transaction, you must send the agreed amount and type of Digital Tokens. TFH does not process user’s Digital Tokens or traditional currency and does not perform any transfers on behalf of users. TFH does not handle, manage, oversee, verify or provide any sort of warranty over any transactions. In the event where the transaction is not received, reversed, improperly processed, or otherwise encountered an error, you and the third-party providers must work together to resolve any issue. Any disputes, claims, losses, misunderstandings, technical errors, or issues of any kind (both accidental and allegedly intentional) related to payments or transactions must be dealt directly between you and the third-party provider. TFH bears no responsibility whatsoever and will not be a party to any payment-related disputes or discussions, nor is it liable for any losses or damages the parties involved may incur.
You are solely responsible for accepting the risk of any price fluctuations regarding the value of Digital Tokens, and understand that by the time you complete a transaction, the value of the Digital Tokens involved in the transaction may have changed significantly.
2.14.2 Third-Party.
Products and services displayed in any miniapp are offered and managed by third-parties. By using Miniapps, you acknowledge and agree that:
These Terms are between you and us, and not with any specific miniapp;
You are accessing an app developed and/or provided by a third-party app, which party is solely responsible for the miniapp;
TFH only provides access to third-party payment providers via World App wallet, and does not itself process payments or hold funds;
The miniapps may have additional terms as a part of their products or services with which you must comply if you are accepting their service; and
You fully acknowledge and explicitly assume any and all risks related to the transactions, and agree that we shall not be liable for any risks or adverse consequences arising from such transactions.
The individual Developers of the miniapps available at Miniapps are solely responsible for the content, products, goods, or services made available to you directly via their respective miniapps. For any queries or disputes you shall contact the respective Developer directly.
Users accept all risks related to making a transaction, including the risk that they will not receive the proceeds of their purchase or sale. In the event of a problem in regards to any transaction, TFH is not able to assist with a resolution, nor holds any liability for problems arising from any transactions.
2.14.3 TFH Fees.
We may add a fee for using Miniapps when you make a transaction with a Developer. The amount of this fee will be displayed to you within the platform. Any such fees will be displayed and current as reflected in Miniapps and may be updated and changed from time to time.
2.14.4 Taxes.
It is your sole responsibility to determine whether, and to what extent, any taxes apply to any transaction via Miniapps or any transactions you make therein, and to withhold, collect, report and remit the correct amount of tax to the appropriate tax authorities.
2.14.5 No general monitoring.
TFH will have no general obligation to monitor the information generated by users, nor actively to seek facts or circumstances indicating any illegal activity within Miniapps.
However, if we become aware, irrespective of the means used, that an illegal product or service has been offered via Miniapps to users located in the European Union, we shall inform the users that have purchased the illegal product or service through Miniapps.
2.14.6 Prohibited Activities.
Users of Miniapps Services agree not to post or distribute any content that violates any laws or infringes any third-party rights, including but not limited to any intellectual property rights, privacy rights, or rights of publicity.
Also, you agree to not engage in any activities that:
Are unlawful, fraudulent, or harmful;
Interfere with or disrupt the operation of Miniapps;
Violate any terms set forth in our App Guidelines; and
Include content not permitted under the App Guidelines.
2.14.7 Flagging of illegal content.
World App has easy to access and user-friendly mechanisms for users to notify us of illegal content in the Miniapps platform. We will act expeditiously to review such reports.
2.14.8 Removal of illegal content.
If we determine that any miniapp contains illegal content or offers illegal products or services, it shall be removed from Miniapps. TFH will provide a brief, clear and specific statement of reasons to any poster of illegal content or services.
Any restriction enforced by World App to its users will be done diligently, objectively and proportionately.
Users who believe their content has been removed or access to it has been disabled unjustifiably can contact us via
legalnotice@toolsforhumanity.com
to appeal the decision. We provide a free, electronic complaint system enabling users to challenge our decisions related to content removal, service suspension, account termination, or monetization restrictions due to alleged illegal content or terms violations.
2.14.9 Content moderation.
TFH reserves the right to suspend, for a reasonable period of time and after having issued a prior warning where legally required to do so, the provision of our services to users that frequently provide manifestly illegal content. TFH also may temporarily suspend processing of notices and complaints from users frequently submitting unfounded claims.
2.15 Usernames
