Services
2.1 Operator Agreement
We partner with local independent contractors called “Orb Operators,” who facilitate user signups and help answer questions you may have about us. These Orb Operators receive training and are knowledgeable about Worldcoin.
Upon satisfaction of certain requirements, as defined by TFH from time to time, and at its sole discretion, TFH may elect you to enter into an operator agreement, whereby, among other things, we would be entrusting you with one or more Orbs for the purpose of signing up users in your region.
2.2 Orb App
TFH, at its sole discretion, may allow you to access the Orb App that allows you to monitor certain activity and statistics relevant to you and your business as Orb Operator. We may also make certain features available to help you conduct your business as Orb Operator. Access to the Orb App, and certain features within the Orb App, may be unavailable or restricted, depending on your location. It is your responsibility to make sure that your use of the Services is legal where you use them. Services are not available in all languages.
2.3 Independent Contractors.
We do not control your performance of the Services. You and any persons who assist you, including any field staff, are independent contractors and not our employees. You are free to engage in other businesses so long as such engagement does not create a conflict of interest or impact your ability to perform under a potential operator agreement. No course of dealing between TFH and you, will be construed to create or imply an employment or agency relationship, or a partnership or joint-venturer relationship between the TFH and you or, between TFH and your employees or agents, including field staff. Neither TFH nor you has the authority to bind the other, to incur any liability, or otherwise act on behalf of the other. You acknowledge and agree that you have no authority to alter or modify this User Terms and Conditions or the Marketing Guidelines or our IP, or to make any express or implied warranties of any kind regarding the Orb, WLD, or the Worldcoin network. Each Party will be solely responsible for payment of its employees' or contractors’ (including Sub-Operators’) wages or salaries (including withholding of income taxes, social security, and any other taxes), workers' compensation, and all other employment benefits in compliance with applicable laws. You ensure compliance with the terms of the Agreement by any Sub-Operators who assist you during the Contract Period, and you will be solely liable for the actions or inactions of such Sub-Operators or any conflicts arising out of your relationship with such Sub-Operators.
2.3 Orb Operator Training
While Orb Operators receive constant and frequent training, you hereby acknowledge and accept we have no control over Orb Operator’s statements, behavior and conduct and we disclaim all liability for any consequence derived therefrom.
2.4 Payment Term
We may agree to pay your signup rewards and other payments in fiat currency or in cryptocurrencies such as WLD. We may update the payment amount and type upon notice to you. For payments in fiat currency such as Euro or US Dollars, we may require you to provide an invoice detailing the number of signups per day, dates of signup, and the amounts earned in fiat currency. Unless otherwise stated in an invoice, we will pay the undisputed amount in the invoice within 45 days from the date of receipt. We may also impose certain requirements to earn the rewards or bonuses based on your performance or user actions. We will provide the requirements on the Website. We may reasonably adjust or withhold all or a portion of payment owed to you (i) if we believe that you have attempted to defraud or abuse us or the users or (ii) in order to resolve a user complaint.
2.5 Records.
You may be required to keep complete and accurate records related to your operations under the Operator Agreement. Such records must include, at minimum, expenses incurred and amounts received related to Orb operations, the transacting parties, transaction descriptions, and the transaction dates. We may inspect your books and records in order to verify the financial situation of the Orb Operator and to ensure compliance with applicable regulatory requirements (“Audit”). You will make a reasonable effort to provide records and personnel familiar with the records to us. During such Audit, we may take extracts or make copies of your records as it deems necessary. Notwithstanding the foregoing, we may at any time require you to provide us with your latest financial statements and an overview of your financial status.
